casebody.data:
DOHERTY, Respondent, v. LORD et al., Appellants. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 17, 1894.) Action by John Doherty against Samuel Lord, Jr., and another.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

Henry Tompkins, for appellants. W. T. B. Millican, for respondent.

No opinion. Motion for reargument denied, with $10 costs. See 25 N. Y. Supp. 752; 28 N. Y. Supp. 720.
